-- Speed Reducers
(1, 'ATR150XL', 'ATR150XL.jpg',	3234.00,	'The ATR150XL is designed for use on the XL150S, XL150SC, XL125S and XL125RC. The lever-actuated system has one neutral and four resistance positions when used on the XL150S, XL150SC and XL125RC and on the XL125S it has 1 neutral and 3 resistance positions. The machined aluminum roller arms and lever make it very light and strong while nylon rollers and bushings reduce noise. Dual bearings ensure solid contact with the wheels and it works well in both wet and dry conditions. The lever actuated system is easy to engage for increased training resistance or for slowing the skis when negotiating moderately steep downhill’s. For steep terrain we recommend the use of a brake.'),
(1, 'ATR900XL', 'ATRXL900.jpg',	3234.00,	'The ATR900XL is designed for use on the XL900, XLC900, and XL98RC series of skis.  The stainless steel roller arms and machined aluminum lever make it light and strong and the nylon bushings reduce noise. Dual bearings ensure solid contact with the wheels and it works well in both wet and dry conditions. The lever actuated system has one neutral and four resistance positions that is easy to engage whether for increased training resistance or for slowing the skis when approaching moderately steep hills. For steep terrain we recommend the use of a brake.'),
(1, 'ATR9848',	'ATR9848.jpg',	3234.00,	'The ATR9848 is specifically designed for use on the XL9848. The stainless steel roller arms and machined aluminum lever make it light and strong while nylon rollers and bushings reduce noise. Dual bearings ensure solid contact with the wheels and it works well in both wet and dry conditions. The lever actuated system has one neutral and four resistance positions that is easy to engage for training or for slowing the skis when negotiating moderately steep downhill’s. For steep terrain we recommend the use of a brake.'),
(1,	'ATRA',		'ATRA.jpg',		1782.00,	'The ATRA (Advanced Training Resistance Aluminum) Speed Reducer has a machined aluminum bearing retainer for the best heat dissipation and strength. The lever actuated system has one neutral and four resistance positions that is easy to engage whether for increasing resistance or for slowing the skis down when negotiating moderate downhill’s. For steep terrain we recommend the use of a brake.'),
(1,	'ATRXL98',	'ATRXL98.jpg',	3234.00,	'The ATRXL98 is designed for use on the XL98R and XL98SL.  The stainless steel roller arms and machined aluminum lever make it light and strong while nylon rollers and bushings reduce noise. Dual bearings ensure solid contact with the wheels and it works well in both wet and dry conditions. The lever actuated system ensures even pressure distribution and has one neutral and four resistance positions that is easy to engage for increased training resistance or for slowing the skis when negotiating moderate downhill’s. For steep terrain we recommend the use of a brake.'),

-- Brakes
(2, 'B900',		'B900.jpg',		3927.00,	'Universal Brakes are designed for the V2 900, 900K, and 800 series skis and most pre XL style V2 Skis. The Universal brakes are mounted directly into the shaft so some drilling is required. If bindings have already been mounted they may need to be moved forward if there is not sufficient room for the brake.'),
(2, 'B125RC',	'B125RC.jpg',	4257.00,	'Universal Brakes are designed for the V2 900, 900K, and 800 series skis and most pre XL style V2 Skis. The Universal brakes are mounted directly into the shaft so some drilling is required. If bindings have already been mounted they may need to be moved forward if there is not sufficient room for the brake.'),
(2, 'B150',		'B150.jpg',		3927.00,	'Universal Brakes are designed for the V2 900, 900K, and 800 series skis and most pre XL style V2 Skis. The Universal brakes are mounted directly into the shaft so some drilling is required. If bindings have already been mounted they may need to be moved forward if there is not sufficient room for the brake.'),
(2,	'B900XL',	'B900XL.jpg',	2277.00,	'The XL Brakes are designed for all V2 XL style models and easily mount in the pre-drilled holes on the rear fork making them much lighter and easier to install than the original V2 brakes.'),
(2,	'BXL125RC',	'BXL125RC.jpg',	2607.00,	'The XL Brakes are designed for all V2 XL style models and easily mount in the pre-drilled holes on the rear fork making them much lighter and easier to install than the original V2 brakes.'),
(2,	'B100XL',	'B100XL.jpg',	2277.00,	'The XL Brakes are designed for all V2 XL style models and easily mount in the pre-drilled holes on the rear fork making them much lighter and easier to install than the original V2 brakes. B100XL is designed for use on the XL98R and XL98SL and mounts directly in the pre-drilled holes in the rear fork.'),
(2,	'B150XL',	'B150XL.jpg',	2277.00,	'The XL Brakes are designed for all V2 XL style models and easily mount in the pre-drilled holes on the rear fork making them much lighter and easier to install than the original V2 brakes. B150XL is designed for use on the XL150S, XL150SC, XL125S and the XL9848.'),

